    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T18:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T18:36:00-05:00" n="660"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11988.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>U S. S. <hi rend="italic">Florida, <lb/> Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have informed Embassy of Mayo’s message in regard to arrest of boat’s crew and
                    suggested that the gravity of the offense be explained to Huerta and promise of
                    ample reparation be obtained, to avoid forcing the issue locally at Tampico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
